WEBVTT

00:01.302 --> 00:03.150
Previously on
"Desperate Housewives"...

00:03.174 --> 00:04.761
My husband died
thinking that I murdered him.

00:04.785 --> 00:07.014
Bree put the past behind her.

00:07.038 --> 00:09.086
You keep me on as your lawyer,
your wife's off-limits.

00:09.110 --> 00:10.317
He's my lawyer.

00:10.341 --> 00:12.419
While Carlos gambled
with his future...

00:12.443 --> 00:14.670
How much money do you think
you'll need to get to Utah?

00:14.693 --> 00:16.023
Susan interfered

00:16.047 --> 00:18.187
with a family reunion.

00:20.521 --> 00:25.032
George Williams
had never been lucky in love.

00:25.056 --> 00:27.034
It seemed that the women
he dated

00:27.058 --> 00:32.179
always invented reasons not to
consummate their relationship.

00:32.203 --> 00:36.713
Um, I'm afraid
we'd wake my roommate.

00:38.739 --> 00:44.020
Uh, I have to get up
really early for work.

00:45.546 --> 00:48.595
I'm, uh, saving myself...

00:48.619 --> 00:51.158
For... marriage.

00:52.383 --> 00:54.361
Sadly for George,

00:54.385 --> 00:59.106
it was one unoriginal excuse
after another.

01:00.461 --> 01:04.671
But since he'd starting
seeing Bree Van De Kamp,

01:04.694 --> 01:07.144
George couldn't help but feel...

01:07.168 --> 01:09.146
Hi. The kids are gone.

01:09.170 --> 01:12.149
We have the house
all to ourselves tonight.

01:12.173 --> 01:16.083
His luck was about to change.

01:16.107 --> 01:18.255
I thought the duck
turned out well,

01:18.279 --> 01:20.257
although the sauce
was a little bit thick.

01:20.281 --> 01:22.759
But judging by how many helpings
you had,

01:22.783 --> 01:24.793
I think I got away with it.

01:27.188 --> 01:28.235
Mmm.

01:28.259 --> 01:29.766
Mmm.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.638
What are you thinking about?

01:31.662 --> 01:33.092
Your hair.

01:36.527 --> 01:38.645
Would you mind if I...

01:38.669 --> 01:41.569
Uh, no. Go ahead.

01:48.279 --> 01:50.179
Is that better?

02:03.294 --> 02:05.504
That was nice.

02:10.401 --> 02:13.680
It's okay
that I'm doing this, right?

02:13.704 --> 02:16.691
Well, I thought we were gonna
let the duck digest a bit more,

02:16.715 --> 02:18.415
but what the heck?

02:20.771 --> 02:21.748
Oh!

02:21.772 --> 02:22.849
What's wrong?

02:22.873 --> 02:24.796
I don't know.
I felt something weird.

02:24.820 --> 02:28.255
Oh, that was my tongue.
It extends farther than most.

02:28.279 --> 02:31.127
I should have warned you. No,
no, no, it wasn't your kiss.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.400
I felt something weird
on my neck.

02:36.887 --> 02:38.365
Wh-what are you doing?

02:38.389 --> 02:40.867
I don't know. I'm just
really starting to itch.

02:40.891 --> 02:43.431
Oh.

02:44.635 --> 02:46.213
What is it?

02:46.237 --> 02:48.837
Y-You've got a huge rash.

02:56.807 --> 02:58.785
It's starting to spread
to my face.

02:58.809 --> 03:01.188
Are you allergic
to something you ate?

03:01.212 --> 03:03.260
Oh, I don't think so.

03:03.284 --> 03:05.871
I mean, I've made duck I'orange
a thousand times.

03:05.895 --> 03:08.235
Something is causing that rash.

03:08.259 --> 03:09.796
Bree, Bree, please don't.

03:09.820 --> 03:12.299
I'm sorry, George,
but you have to go.

03:12.323 --> 03:13.800
But the kids are away.

03:13.824 --> 03:15.907
I was sort of hoping
we could make love tonight.

03:15.931 --> 03:17.904
How are we gonna do that,
George?

03:17.928 --> 03:20.247
You have just given me hives.

03:21.532 --> 03:23.210
Though painful to hear,

03:23.234 --> 03:24.521
George had to admit,

03:24.545 --> 03:28.255
at least this excuse
was original.

03:28.279 --> 03:36.279
