04:11.682 --> 04:17.303
It's a fact that little girls
dream of big white weddings.

04:17.327 --> 04:22.969
Of course, the exact same thing
can be said for big girls,

04:22.993 --> 04:27.344
some of whom
can get incredibly anxious

04:27.368 --> 04:30.016
waiting for the boys
in their lives

04:30.040 --> 04:33.550
to make those dreams come true.

04:33.574 --> 04:35.522
Aah! Oh. Watch it, susie.

04:35.546 --> 04:38.024
Mom, why don't you just
go see a dressmaker?

04:38.048 --> 04:40.457
Wait. I have the perfect idea.

04:40.481 --> 04:43.560
You get in the dress,
and I'll pin it.

04:43.584 --> 04:45.562
We wear the same size.

04:45.586 --> 04:46.863
Since when?

04:46.887 --> 04:49.536
Since forever.

04:49.560 --> 04:52.038
You have to leave, though.
You can't stay.

04:52.062 --> 04:54.040
You can't see susie
in a wedding dress,

04:54.064 --> 04:56.042
not untilyourbig day.

04:56.066 --> 04:59.045
Mom! No, it's not a problem.

04:59.069 --> 05:00.807
I can see her in it.

05:00.831 --> 05:01.808
You can?

05:01.832 --> 05:03.310
You can?

05:03.334 --> 05:05.921
I assume you wanna pick out
your own wedding dress

05:05.945 --> 05:07.914
when we get married, right?

05:07.938 --> 05:10.286
That sounds like
a proposal.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.458
Did it?

05:11.482 --> 05:12.759
Yeah, it did.

05:12.783 --> 05:14.761
Huh. What do you know?

05:14.785 --> 05:17.324
Are you planning
to pop the question?

05:17.348 --> 05:19.326
Well, if she knows it's coming,

05:19.350 --> 05:21.768
the question won't really pop,
now will it?

05:21.792 --> 05:24.776
He's right, mom. I want it
to be just like you do...

05:24.800 --> 05:26.603
You know, on your own terms,

05:26.627 --> 05:29.906
and you get down on one knee and
the whole production. That's the plan.

05:29.930 --> 05:31.908
Well, then I can wait.
I can wait.

05:31.932 --> 05:34.611
I'm a good waiter. Good.

05:34.635 --> 05:36.843
I'm just wondering if there's
a ballpark of how long

05:36.867 --> 05:39.686
I will have to wait...
A week, a month, after lunch?

05:39.710 --> 05:42.349
Again, you're not waiting
for the pop.

05:42.373 --> 05:44.351
Right, right. I'm sorry.

05:44.375 --> 05:46.022
Yay!

05:46.046 --> 05:48.955
Oh, mom.

05:48.979 --> 05:52.929
So the hives occurred
right after you kissed George?

05:52.953 --> 05:55.932
Yes. It was the strangest thing,

05:55.956 --> 05:58.835
and so inconvenient.

05:58.859 --> 06:00.407
To be honest,

06:00.431 --> 06:03.540
I think we were about to
make love for the first time.

06:03.564 --> 06:05.547
Bree, have you considered
the idea

06:05.571 --> 06:07.343
that your subconscious mind

06:07.367 --> 06:09.376
was trying to sabotage
your evening with George?

06:09.400 --> 06:11.378
Actually,
I have not considered that

06:11.402 --> 06:13.880
because that's idiotic.

06:13.904 --> 06:15.887
You don't think being
with George

06:15.911 --> 06:18.425
made you feel a bit guilty?
Why should I feel guilty?

06:18.449 --> 06:21.027
Perhaps you felt you were
about to commit adultery.

06:21.051 --> 06:25.591
Dr. Goldfine, Rex is dead.
You can't cheat on a corpse.

06:28.088 --> 06:30.897
Well, maybe that's not how
you really feel deep down.

06:30.921 --> 06:33.570
Oh, so you think I'm crazy?

06:33.594 --> 06:36.408
You say you got
a case of hives for no reason.

06:36.432 --> 06:38.104
I think there is a reason,

06:38.128 --> 06:40.447
and it's probably
a psychosomatic one.

06:40.471 --> 06:41.908
You can think whatever you want,

06:41.932 --> 06:44.416
but to be honest, I don't
believe in the subconscious.

06:44.440 --> 06:46.813
Every time you've said "Rex"
in this session,

06:46.837 --> 06:49.816
you've stroked the place where
your wedding ring used to be.

06:49.840 --> 06:52.040
Why did you do that?

06:56.487 --> 06:57.564
Let's talk about Monday.

06:57.588 --> 06:59.796
We are re-pitching
to the kamarov people.

06:59.820 --> 07:02.068
Lynette, you'll be on point.

07:02.092 --> 07:03.530
Great. Great. No problem.

07:03.554 --> 07:05.532
And can you do me a favor

07:05.556 --> 07:07.874
and maybenotwear the green suit?

07:07.898 --> 07:09.576
Um...

07:09.600 --> 07:14.711
I... wasn't planning to,
uh, but... why?

07:14.735 --> 07:17.684
The fabric. It just has
this quality to it,

07:17.708 --> 07:20.046
like you could... I don't know...

07:20.070 --> 07:23.750
Wipe it clean with a damp cloth.

07:23.774 --> 07:25.761
I'll just wear
a different suit, then.

07:25.785 --> 07:27.724
Great.

07:27.748 --> 07:29.996
Like what, you think?

07:30.020 --> 07:32.459
Another suit.
I have other suits.

07:32.483 --> 07:34.910
And if by other suits,
you mean the gray one,

07:34.934 --> 07:37.704
then of course you do.

07:37.728 --> 07:40.106
No, actually,
I have quite a few others.

07:40.130 --> 07:42.669
Uh, the blue one

07:42.693 --> 07:44.611
and, uh...

07:44.635 --> 07:46.673
What's wrong with the blue suit?

07:46.697 --> 07:48.875
Stu, would you like
to tell Lynette

07:48.899 --> 07:50.999
what's wrong with the blue suit?

07:52.472 --> 07:54.681
No. That's cool.

07:54.705 --> 07:56.853
Stu... come on.

07:56.877 --> 07:58.555
Do the thing...

07:58.579 --> 08:00.687
The thing that you did at lunch.

08:00.711 --> 08:03.089
"Look at me. I'm Lynette."

08:03.113 --> 08:06.563
"I've got food stains
everywhere."

08:06.587 --> 08:09.566
All right. So if I get
my blue suit dry-cleaned,

08:09.590 --> 08:11.638
will that be acceptable
to everyone?

08:11.662 --> 08:15.602
The pants also have
a split seam in the back.

08:22.202 --> 08:23.610
Excuse me.

08:24.635 --> 08:26.152
Hello, David.

08:26.176 --> 08:28.154
What the hell is this?

08:28.178 --> 08:30.156
I thought I told you
to dress maternal.

08:30.180 --> 08:33.159
Yes, you did, and I considered
it for about a second.

08:33.183 --> 08:34.220
What happened?

08:34.244 --> 08:36.227
David, I know you're
the lawyer and all,

08:36.251 --> 08:38.995
but trust me, it's never a smart
strategy to cover this up.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.996
We've got 40 minutes
before the pre-trial hearing.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.999
Let's go home
and get you changed.

08:43.023 --> 08:45.006
What? You want to get
your husband out of jail?

08:45.030 --> 08:47.503
You gotta dress like
a pregnant, suffering wife,

08:47.527 --> 08:50.537
not the cover of "vogue." David.

08:50.561 --> 08:52.539
Louis, what are you doing
here? I need a favor, David.

08:52.563 --> 08:55.687
If this has to do with lifting
my client's restraining order,

08:55.711 --> 08:57.684
the answer's the same one
you got last week.

08:57.708 --> 08:59.185
You don't understand.
I love crystal.

08:59.209 --> 09:02.088
Yeah, we all love the pretty
ladies at the stop n' shop,

09:02.112 --> 09:04.596
but now you've gotta love her
from 50 yards away.

09:04.620 --> 09:07.624
You turned her against me.
If it wasn't for you,

09:07.648 --> 09:09.756
we'd be together.
Louis, crystal hired me

09:09.780 --> 09:12.699
to keep you away from her.
She doesn'twantto see you.

09:12.723 --> 09:14.936
Oh, yeah, then why did
she ask for my phone number?

09:14.960 --> 09:16.733
She's a cashier.
You paid by check.

09:16.757 --> 09:18.735
It doesn't make you special.

09:18.759 --> 09:21.638
Don't walk away from me.
We're having a conversation!

09:21.662 --> 09:23.970
Louis, this is your problem.

09:23.994 --> 09:26.017
You're creepy! Nobody likes you.

09:26.041 --> 09:28.845
What you call a conversation
the rest of us call harassment.

09:28.869 --> 09:31.669
You want a friend,
get a hamster.

09:33.644 --> 09:35.081
David!

09:35.105 --> 09:36.605
Aah!

09:42.713 --> 09:43.930
Call the police!

09:43.954 --> 09:45.624
Stay there!

09:55.696 --> 09:57.744
That's right, you better run,

09:57.768 --> 10:00.647
'cause I'm gonna get
some bullets for this thing

10:00.671 --> 10:02.048
and come after you! Freeze!

10:02.072 --> 10:04.310
Hey, everything's cool.

10:04.334 --> 10:06.212
Aah!

10:10.741 --> 10:12.341
Are you okay?

10:23.623 --> 10:28.374
Weeds are a common annoyance
of life in suburbia,

10:28.398 --> 10:31.998
and no matter how hard
we try to get rid of them...

10:33.664 --> 10:36.674
They always tend to crop
back up.

10:39.009 --> 10:41.087
A-Are you seeing this?

10:41.111 --> 10:44.190
I don't believe him.
He is so brazen.

10:44.214 --> 10:47.854
He's just mowing the lawn
like nothing ever happened.

10:47.878 --> 10:50.857
What should we do? Should we
call the police? Well, Susan did say

10:50.881 --> 10:53.700
that he murdered Mrs. Huber,
so my vote would be yes.

10:53.724 --> 10:56.194
Oh, my god, Susan's home.

11:02.693 --> 11:04.943
Has she seen Paul yet?

11:10.170 --> 11:12.700
I think so.

11:20.680 --> 11:21.928
Hello, Susan.

11:21.952 --> 11:24.831
Oh, my god. Paul.

11:24.855 --> 11:26.863
Need some help with those bags?

11:26.887 --> 11:31.197
Why... are you doing here?

11:31.221 --> 11:34.771
This is where I live.
I came home to find my son.

11:35.996 --> 11:38.845
Here you go.
No, don't come near me.

11:38.869 --> 11:41.708
I'm just giving you back your pie
filling. I don't want my pie filling.

11:41.732 --> 11:43.980
Oh, come on. Just take it.
No, stop!

11:44.004 --> 11:46.452
Put that pie filling down.

11:46.476 --> 11:48.815
Slowly.

11:48.839 --> 11:50.717
I'm calling 9-1-1.
You don't want to do that.

11:50.741 --> 11:54.290
Oh, I think I do.
You're a cold-blooded murderer.

11:54.314 --> 11:57.424
Susan, how can you believe that?
We've been neighbors for years.

11:59.790 --> 12:01.868
Ladies, good to see you.

12:01.892 --> 12:03.429
Paul, we've called the police.

12:03.453 --> 12:05.772
You didn't really need
to do that.

12:05.796 --> 12:07.804
We know what you did
to Mrs. Huber.

12:07.828 --> 12:10.306
Wonderful. I see you've all
turned into Susan

12:10.330 --> 12:12.000
while I've been gone.

12:15.135 --> 12:17.844
Oh, thank god. They're here.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.751
Hey, what's going on?

12:24.775 --> 12:26.322
Oh, Mayer's convinced

12:26.346 --> 12:28.494
that Paul young murdered
Martha Huber.

12:28.518 --> 12:30.496
Oh, my god.
I live right behind him.

12:30.520 --> 12:34.300
I know. I gave him
my house keys to feed my cat.

12:34.324 --> 12:38.835
I win. I made out with him.

12:38.859 --> 12:41.768
Here you go. There's no warrant
here for a Paul young.

12:41.792 --> 12:44.070
Why don't you ask Mike?
He overheard everything, right?

12:44.094 --> 12:45.817
Who's Mike?
Uh, he's my boyfriend,

12:45.841 --> 12:48.815
and he told me that Paul
confessed everything to him.

12:48.839 --> 12:50.777
Oh, and Mike has
Martha's journals,

12:50.801 --> 12:52.919
which clearly prove
that Paul had a motive.

12:52.943 --> 12:55.927
All right, all right, where do I find
this Mike guy? Uh, he's... follow me.

12:55.951 --> 12:59.025
You mind if I stay here?
I've got a lot of raking to do.

12:59.049 --> 13:01.349
Let's go.

13:08.058 --> 13:11.888
Hey.

13:13.393 --> 13:15.501
What's going on?

13:15.525 --> 13:17.403
Mike, Paul young is back.

13:17.427 --> 13:19.497
Look.

13:28.208 --> 13:32.118
Your girlfriend said Mr. Young
confessed a murder to you?

13:32.142 --> 13:34.891
Um...

13:34.915 --> 13:38.294
No. No, not to me.

13:38.318 --> 13:40.396
And I don't suppose you have
a journal that belonged

13:40.420 --> 13:42.798
to a Martha Huber?

13:42.822 --> 13:44.400
No. I hardly knew her.

13:44.424 --> 13:47.911
Besides, you ever known a woman
who'd loan out her diary?

13:47.935 --> 13:49.836
Mike, what are you doing?

13:49.860 --> 13:52.808
I'm sorry, Susan. I don't know
what you're talking about.

13:52.832 --> 13:55.889
But I've got a job to get to.
Is there anything else?

13:55.913 --> 13:58.606
No, no,
that pretty much covers it.

14:14.384 --> 14:16.371
Well, someone might as well
say it.

14:16.395 --> 14:19.456
Susan, what the hell
have you been smoking?

14:24.895 --> 14:27.165
Ahem. Okay.

14:29.369 --> 14:31.017
Wow!

14:31.041 --> 14:32.848
Nice.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.921
Oh, my god.

14:34.945 --> 14:37.353
Okay, don't be distracted
by that. Look atme.

14:37.377 --> 14:38.885
Here I am tomorrow,

14:38.909 --> 14:41.087
making my presentation.

14:41.111 --> 14:44.860
You see?
You see how it moves with me?

14:44.884 --> 14:46.893
That's where themagicis.

14:46.917 --> 14:49.335
$900?

14:49.359 --> 14:51.337
Yeah, well, this one was
the most expensive.

14:51.361 --> 14:53.339
The other ones aren't as nice.
But look.

14:53.363 --> 14:56.380
Look, look, look, look at me,
look at me. Watch.

14:56.404 --> 14:58.905
I don't walk in it. I glide.

14:58.929 --> 15:01.978
Um, honey, you know what?

15:02.002 --> 15:04.986
There's gotta be like
$3,000 worth of clothes here.

15:05.010 --> 15:08.014
Yeah, well, I haven't bought
a new suit in six years.

15:08.038 --> 15:09.515
So? When I was working,

15:09.539 --> 15:11.958
you don't think I would have
loved to have a designer suit?

15:11.982 --> 15:13.419
I wore wash-and-wear

15:13.443 --> 15:15.426
so that we could live
in a nice neighborhood,

15:15.450 --> 15:17.964
so we could take the kids
on vacation every summer.

15:17.988 --> 15:21.097
I mean, I made sacrifices.
I'm willing to make sacrifices.

15:21.121 --> 15:23.099
Great, well, let's start here,

15:23.123 --> 15:26.010
because this should cover
a math tutor for Parker.

15:26.034 --> 15:28.004
Whoa, hold on a sec.

15:28.028 --> 15:30.076
Six months of preschool
for penny.

15:30.100 --> 15:32.038
All right, now you're being ridiculous.
You know what? And the twins...

15:32.062 --> 15:34.540
They're gonna need braces.
That oughta make a dent.

15:34.564 --> 15:38.945
Oh, no. Come on, Tom.
Not this one.

15:38.969 --> 15:41.087
Strip.

15:41.111 --> 15:44.050
You saw the walk, right?

15:44.074 --> 15:46.993
You wanna see the walk again?

15:47.017 --> 15:49.325
I'll tutor Parker myself.

15:49.349 --> 15:51.027
Honey, that'd be great.

15:51.051 --> 15:53.121
You also gonna take up
home dentistry?

16:02.032 --> 16:04.732
Fine. I'll take them back.

16:07.237 --> 16:10.137
Could you step out
for a minute, please?

16:12.002 --> 16:15.482
I want to be alone with it
for a little while.

16:33.093 --> 16:34.370
Hi, it's Bree.

16:34.394 --> 16:36.447
Hi. I was thinking
about calling you.

16:36.471 --> 16:39.445
I just got some new
antihistamines in at the store.

16:39.469 --> 16:42.148
I think they're really gonna
help with your rash.

16:42.172 --> 16:45.156
Well, great. Um, how would
you feel about the two of us

16:45.180 --> 16:47.653
checking into a romantic hotel
tomorrow?

16:47.677 --> 16:52.118
What? Uh, i-I'd like that
very much.

16:52.142 --> 16:54.620
I will let you make
all of the arrangements.

16:54.644 --> 16:57.093
Something out of town
would be nice.

16:57.117 --> 17:00.147
Good night.

17:14.104 --> 17:17.183
We need to talk.
Where did you come from?

17:17.207 --> 17:18.483
I'm sorry.
I've been waiting for you.

17:18.508 --> 17:21.117
I'm just a little upset because
everybody thinks I'm crazy.

17:21.141 --> 17:23.189
Can I at least get out
of the truck first?

17:23.213 --> 17:24.589
Yes, definitely.

17:24.614 --> 17:26.097
I mean, I can understand

17:26.121 --> 17:29.355
why you wouldn't want the cops
to know that you kidnapped Paul.

17:29.379 --> 17:31.727
I mean, that definitely looks
bad. Since I was on probation.

17:31.751 --> 17:35.030
Well, right.
I mean, there's that.

17:35.054 --> 17:36.511
And in possession of a gun...

17:36.535 --> 17:39.135
Well, okay...
Which I held to his head.

17:39.159 --> 17:41.437
So I violated my probation,
committed a felony

